This paper proposes a new language model that captures both intra-sentence and inter-sentence dependencies, as well as global semantics. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the natural language processing (NLP) sub-category of computer science, which is cs.CL. Additionally, the paper uses recurrent neural networks (RNNs) and stochastic-gradient MCMC, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper mentions generating diverse sentences and paragraphs, which could involve computer vision techniques (cs.CV) for image captioning or visual question answering.
